<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
Differing from var. 
<taxonomicName authority="brownii" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. brownii" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="brownii">Lilium brownii brownii</taxonomicName>
and var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker, Gardeners Chronicle ser. 3 vol. 10: 225 (22 August" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Baker" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. chloraster" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="chloraster">Lilium brownii chloraster</taxonomicName>
by the dark green obovate-lanceolate to oblanceolate leaves 5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 cm (vs. linear to lanceolate 0.6-1 cm wide). The leaf size also decreases and becomes more sparse towards the apex of the inflorescence than in the other varieties. Corolla colour varies in the degree of colouration from finely chestnut brown markings externally to greenish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">China</emphasis>
: Anhui, Fujian, Gansu, Guangxi, Guizhou, Hebei, Henan, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangsu, Jiangxi, Shaanxi, Shanxi, Sichuan, Yunnan, Zhejiang. It seems that var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker, Gard. Chron. 24: 134 (1 August" authorityYear="1885" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. viridulum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="viridulum">Lilium brownii viridulum</taxonomicName>
does not occur in Guandong Province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Growing along ravines on grassy slopes, in clearings of open forests and amongst low scrub, 100 to 1000 m alt. Flowering in June and July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
